# Python Marketing Data Analysis Templates

This repository contains practical Python templates for marketing and growth analysis.

The goal is to analyze campaign performance using CSV exports from platforms such as Meta Ads, Google Ads, email marketing tools, CRM systems, GA4, or webinar platforms.

## What this project analyzes

- Channel performance
- Campaign performance
- Lead quality
- Webinar show-up rate
- Lead-to-sale conversion
- Cost per lead
- Customer acquisition cost
- ROAS

## Tools used

- Python
- pandas
- matplotlib
- Google Colab / Jupyter Notebook

## Example business questions

- Which channel generates the highest-quality leads?
- Which campaign has the strongest ROAS?
- Where does the funnel break?
- Which audience should receive more budget?
- Which acquisition source brings volume but poor conversion?

## Example KPIs

- Lead to Sale Rate
- Show Up Rate
- Attendee to Sale Rate
- CPL
- CAC
- ROAS

## Repository structure

```text
notebooks/   Python notebooks for analysis
data/        Sample datasets
outputs/     Charts and exported results
notes/       KPI definitions and formulas
